Q: JSON escaping?
Escape the quote/special character with a slash
json.loads('{"story":"once u\\"on a time "}')               # <-- p has been replaced by a quote
json.loads(r'{"story":"once u\"on a time "}')               # <-- raw string

Q: String enclosure in JSON vs Python?
JSON must use double quotes to enclose strings, it cannot use single quotes.
So you must escape every internal quotes
PYTHON: {"blah": ["one", 2, 'th"r"ee']} --> JSON : {"blah": ["one", 2, "th\"r\"ee"]}

